Putin spoke at the board of the Ministry of Internal Affairs.
Important statements:
Only those who respect its traditions, language and culture should be able to come and live in Russia;
Show more
It is necessary to radically update approaches to migration policy;
Those who ordered the terrorist attack at Crocus wanted to split Russia by provoking discord;
It is necessary to improve the efficiency of the police service in the Russian Federation
The recent tragic events at Crocus must not be allowed to provoke a rise in Islamophobia

Vladimir Putin said that the Russian special services will establish all links in the chain in the investigation of the terrorist attack at Crocus City Hall, and also noted the most important areas of work of the Ministry of Internal Affairs. The president outlined the most important areas in the field of ensuring national security. According to the president, special attention must be paid to maintaining public order, suppressing illegal migration, combating extremism and neutralizing criminal groups.

Other statements by Vladimir Putin:

— Security problems are often cross-border in nature, in addition, criminal syndicates often operate in conjunction with foreign intelligence services;

— Today, internal and external threats often intersect and they are directed against our society, containing Russia and undermining its sovereignty;

— The level of security must increase in all constituent entities of the Russian Federation, including in the Donbass and Novorossiya, where they even have to fight with the DRG;

— One of the most important tasks is to strengthen the coordination of law enforcement agencies and intelligence services;

“Under no circumstances should we allow the tragedy in Crocus to be used to provoke national hatred, since this is exactly what the terrorists sought;

“It is especially important to protect the younger generation from the influence of radicals and extremists.
